==English==
===Transitive verb===
'''to [[gloss]] [[over]]'''
# {{idiom}} To [[cover up]] a mistake or a crime; to [[hush up]] or [[whitewash]].
#:''They '''glossed over''' the problem, hoping that the customers wouldn't notice.''
# {{idiom}} To treat something with less [[care]] than it [[deserve]]s; to [[skimp]].
#:''This book only '''glosses over''' quantum mechanics, and doesn't go into detail.''